The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                      
	Bopanna makes   semi-final  
	Atlanta: Rohan Bopanna and Belgian Kristof Vliegen beat Jonathan Erlich and Janko Tipsarevic to book a semi-final berth in the Atlanta Tennis Championships.      
	Paris: Alberto Contador is set to win his third Tour de France title in four years after retaining the yellow jersey in the next-to-last stage on Saturday.       
	Negi draws  
	Biel: Parimarjan Negi played out a draw with Nguyen Ngoc Truong Son of Vietnam in the fifth round of the Young Grandmasters tournament after three losses in the first three rounds and a draw in the fourth.   
	Pallikal out  
	Kuala Lumpur: Indias Dipika Pallikal and Siddharth Suchde bowed out in the first round of Malaysian Open Squash championship in Kuala Lumpur.   
	Modi seeks  
	Mumbai: Suspended IPL chairman Lalit Modi has asked the BCCI disciplinary committee to provide him with minutes of meetings of the special general body of the board and the IPL governing council held after his suspension, sources said.  
	Golf tourney  
	Stockholm: Golfers S.S.P. Chowrasia and Shiv Kapur turned in over-par cards of 73 and 75, respectively, but still managed to advance, following the second round of the Nordea Scandinavian Masters golf tournament.   
	Jeev slips  
	Toronto: Jeev Milkha Singh slipped 16 places to tied 53rd after returning a modest even-par 70, while Arjun Atwal also just about managed to make the cut in the second round of the RBC Canadian Open golf tournament.  
	Friendly tie  
	Madrid: Spain and Argentina will play a friendly in September at River Plates stadium in Buenos Aires.  
	Forlan skips  
	Caracas: Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez says Diego Forlan has had to cancel a visit to the country.  
	Di Stefano ill  
	Madrid: Real Madrid say Alfredo di Stefano (84) has been readmitted to hospital with a heart problem.      
	London: Chelsea striker Didier Drogba will miss next months Community Shield clash with Manchester United and Premier League opener after undergoing groin surgery.         
	Manchester: Nemanja Vidic has agreed a new long-term deal with Manchester United, the club said on Friday.                                                                                                                                                      
